    <item>
      <title>Glassfish 4: Updating Weld</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/posts/glassfish-4-updating-weld/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 30 Jul 2014 15:34:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/posts/glassfish-4-updating-weld/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Updating Weld (&lt;a href=&#34;http://delabassee.com/blog/?p=286%29&#34;&gt;http://delabassee.com/blog/?p=286)&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Grab the Weld 2.0.5 OSGi bundle and copy it to the GF modules directory:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;cp weld-osgi-bundle-2.0.5.Final.jar glassfish/modules/&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Restart GlassFish:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;glassfish/bin/asadmin restart-domain domain1&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You check which version is now installed by issuing:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;glassfish/bin/asadmin osgi lb | grep &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;Weld OSGi&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Glassfish Error: Uncaught exception: java.lang.NullPointerException and Glassfish stops accepting requests on its port</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/posts/glassfish-error-uncaught-exception-java.lang.nullpointerexception-and-glassfish-stops-accepting-requests-on-its-port/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 17 Jul 2014 11:36:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/posts/glassfish-error-uncaught-exception-java.lang.nullpointerexception-and-glassfish-stops-accepting-requests-on-its-port/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;That issue appears in Glassfish 4. It is documented:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://java.net/jira/browse/GRIZZLY-1615?page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel&#34;&gt;GRIZZLY-1615&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://java.net/jira/browse/GLASSFISH-20918?page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel&#34;&gt;GLASSFISH-20918&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You need to download the patch in the second URL and overwrite the file:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;mv nucleus-grizzly-all.jar.1 nucleus-grizzly-all.jar&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Glassfish 4 tricks on CentOS 6</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/posts/glassfish-4-tricks-on-centos-6/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 05 Mar 2014 15:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/posts/glassfish-4-tricks-on-centos-6/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Three tricks here.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;One. Init.d script for CentOS 6:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;script src=&#34;https://gist.github.com/vicendominguez/9089718.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Two. Changing umask permission in Glassfish 4:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Add &amp;ldquo;umask 002&amp;rdquo; just before the &amp;ldquo;exec&amp;rdquo; line in $GLASSFISH_HOME/bin/asadmin&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Three. Changing general logging file in Glassfish 4:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Change logging.properties file line to (by example):&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;com.sun.enterprise.server.logging.GFFileHandler.file=/var/log/glassfish/server.log&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Firewall rules to redirect Glassfish 4.0 ports (80,443,8080 and 8181 will be open to internet)</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/posts/firewall-rules-to-redirect-glassfish-4.0-ports-804438080-and-8181-will-be-open-to-internet/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 19 Feb 2014 12:27:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/posts/firewall-rules-to-redirect-glassfish-4.0-ports-804438080-and-8181-will-be-open-to-internet/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello!&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Fast trick to redirect ports when you are using a Java application server.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;script src=&#34;https://gist.github.com/vicendominguez/8978478.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Be careful because 80, 443, 8080 and 8181 ports will be open to the Internet. If you want to close the 8080 and 8181, you will need an AJP proxy or to mark packets in the firewall. Read this link:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/11065124/iptables-redirect-80-to-8080-but-block-public-8080-access&#34;&gt;Stack Overflow&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;:)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
